reviews.review: It's a good conclusion to what was done before it, it helps fill in holes left by the disastrous last jedi and gives closure to the saga, overall it's funny action packed and emotional, best starwars movie I've seen in a while

Finished the Skywalker Saga contradicting about 6 movies worth of story. Hail Mary attempt to fix the Last Jedi. Relies on future novelizations to cover plot holes unexplained. Palp needed more screen time. Meh.
Hard to follow with so many unanswered questions and leaving holes in the movie. Just seemed piecemeal.  Really did not end leaves a lot to be continued for a new & future generation.

That is sarcasm I don't really mean the thanks when some people kill what I love when I was a child.

As a non Star Wars fan I have seen the previous films and this movie does tend to add on to it previous films in a way and wrap things up pretty nicely with decent action and some really good performances come out at times. The flaws are a bit obvious as Abrams is trying to end the trilogy the way he wanted it started even though the last film doesn’t quite follow the path he laid down. Take your children they will have a good time plus for those who are fans I’m pretty sure they are going to enjoy the fan service throughout.
I couldn’t have hoped for a better note to end on for this trilogy’s conclusion than what I saw today. The whole movie was fabulous and felt complete. Wouldn’t want to miss this movie for anything.

Commercial tat. Unfortunately, Disney have zero respect or affection for the original trilogy as the new trilogy was either entirely pointless retreading or retcon of original films. It’s a shame that studios constantly underestimate an audience’s intelligence and feel that throwing a lot of money on the screen is all that audience’s expect. The two stars are for the technical achievement and the fantastic John Williams score - the characters and plot are all thin and designed to be consumed and disgraced like fast food. This is the McDonald’s of film making.
Too predictable. A lot taken from other movies.
Best Star Wars sequel. A must see for any Star Wars fan.
